GoDrakeBulldogs. com Senior Nick Foster will anchor a Drake defense seeking to spark the Bulldogs to their third consecutive NCAA Tournament appearance in 2010. 1 With 14 starters back, the Drake football team hopes to pick up where it left off last year when the Bulldogs posted an 8-3 record. Only a last-second field goal in the season finale by eventual league champion Butler (20-17) prevented Drake from earning a share of the Pioneer Football League title. “We need to continue to build team chemistry to become better,” said third-year head coach Chris Creighton, who returns 28 letterwinners from last year’s second-place team that posted a 6-2 league mark. “We do have a number of returning letterwinners and starters coming back from a year ago,” said Creighton. “Last year’s team had an intense desire to succeed.
